<span id="freeTextContainer6658607058119771150">If I could give this series of 6 books (I am including the following trilogy) a great many more stars - I would. I first read these when I was 18, first year at college, in hospital for an appendectomy, needed something to read, as a treat my parents got me these - well the first three anyway. I have loved them ever since and have reread them nearly as many times as I have Jane Eyre (yes I know, that&apos;s a strange combination). I love Thomas - I love that he is flawed and selfish and horrible at t</span>
  <span id="freeText6658607058119771150" style="display:none">If I could give this series of 6 books (I am including the following trilogy) a great many more stars - I would. I first read these when I was 18, first year at college, in hospital for an appendectomy, needed something to read, as a treat my parents got me these - well the first three anyway. I have loved them ever since and have reread them nearly as many times as I have Jane Eyre (yes I know, that's a strange combination). I love Thomas - I love that he is flawed and selfish and horrible at times, you can appreciate where all that comes from and it makes the story. The land has more than enough heroes ready to sacrifice everything to balance Thomas' faults. Actually just writing this review makes me want to read them all over again. </span>
  <a data-text-id="6658607058119771150" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

